{"tid":817657,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"與其叫黃種人 不如叫扁鼻種","createTime":"2018-09-13T13:42:10.000Z","updateTime":"2018-09-19T04:06:15.000Z","uid":36058,"like":4,"dislike":6,"uniUserReply":23,"replies":[{"pid":"927cccebef99b5a60c31bc2b8369d0347cc4bc09","tid":817657,"uid":36058,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-09-13T13:42:10.000Z","msg":"18世紀之前，西方人都認為東亞人同屬白人，後來先將東亞人越描越黃。下文簡述當中概要。其實東方人同西方人最大外觀分別唔係膚色，因為南歐人，如葡萄牙、西班牙，好多仲黑過東亞人，反而輪廓先係最大差別，東方人面扁，個鼻最明顯，所以建議扁鼻種。<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<br />\nIt was Johann Friedrich Blumenbach (1752-1840) who went beyond the coloring ascribed by Linnaeus to apply the completely different label of &ldquo;Mongolianness.&rdquo; Regarded as a founder of comparative anatomy, the German zoologist did more than just use the Latin word &ldquo;gilvus,&rdquo; meaning &ldquo;light yellow,&rdquo; to describe East Asian skin color: he also implicated the Mongols, a name with troubling and threatening connotations for Europeans with their memories of Attila the Hun, Genghis Khan, and Timur.<br />\nWhile the references remained anomalous at first, travelers to East Asia gradually began describing locals there more and more as &ldquo;yellow.&rdquo; By the nineteenth century, Keevak argued, the &ldquo;yellow race&rdquo; become a key part of anthropology.<br />\nBut the yellow label came associated with discrimination, exclusion, and violence. Just as no one in the world is purely white or black, neither does anyone actually have skin that is deep yellow. By &ldquo;creating&rdquo; a skin color and investing traits such as &ldquo;Mongolian eyes,&rdquo; the Mongolian birthmark, and mongolism (the old name for Down syndrome), Westerners made the perceived yellow race synonymous with abnormality. They also responded to the arrival of immigrants from Asia by sounding the alarm over the &ldquo;yellow peril&rdquo; - a term with a whole range of negative associations from overpopulation to heathenism, economic competition, and political and social regression. The hidden agenda of this racial color-coding becomes apparent when one considers who benefits from a hierarchy that places &ldquo;yellow&rdquo; and &ldquo;black&rdquo; beneath &ldquo;white.&rdquo;"},{"pid":"957e5780cb5de44a8fa223198a9774db847fb80d","tid":817657,"uid":157362,"like":4,"dislike":14,"score":-10,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-09-13T13:59:03.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"d6d9677f4c0e57b64b49b67ae7c53da31c15d38f","tid":817657,"uid":53466,"like":0,"dislike":9,"score":-9,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-09-13T14:02:25.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"d8b5268bc72751ed3df1b4b280a9cf34b964fa61","tid":817657,"uid":37733,"like":4,"dislike":0,"score":4,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-09-13T14:03:38.000Z","msg":"扁面族"},{"pid":"7df55a336997673e191954beb0ab301cd3accdbd","tid":817657,"uid":121393,"like":31,"dislike":0,"score":31,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-09-13T14:05:44.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"https://img.eservice-hk.net/upload/2018/09/13/220541_b6d40bf089fb453448d31fb7cafa6070.png\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fimg.eservice-hk.net%2Fupload%2F2018%2F09%2F13%2F220541_b6d40bf089fb453448d31fb7cafa6070.png&h=9915d108&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"939d183aef20a34b88392541668214843ac590bc","tid":817657,"uid":157362,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-09-13T14:09:46.000Z","msg":"此回覆已被刪除"},{"pid":"d2b848451bc665de4e0223d8255e3f6dbec5d697","tid":817657,"uid":41245,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-09-13T14:24:10.000Z","msg":"其實應該係半眼皮種"},{"pid":"280b4c10b0abeabffe8468bb7cfd7ef16f103b07","tid":817657,"uid":41375,"like":0,"dislike":2,"score":-2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-09-13T14:28:16.000Z","msg":"唐氏綜合症人種"},{"pid":"7d8f6f840bc4c7e067efa36cbc6f89e15a82d944","tid":817657,"uid":66822,"like":0,"dislike":5,"score":-5,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-09-13T14:34:15.000Z","msg":"唔係個個都扁<br />\n<img src=\"https://img.eservice-hk.net/upload/2018/09/13/223010_f753c3a75140ef4445b7e6826161c842.png\" 